				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It's generally a combination of mid-screen scroll changes (i.e $2005 and $2006 writes) and CHR-ROM bankswitching. To simulate the movement of a flag, for example, you need wavy motion in booth axes, and the most obvious way to do this is to use bankswitching for moving graphics up and down, and scroll changes for the horizontal motion.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

